The paper proposes a novel methodology for deriving expressive features from high-dimensional gene expression data to predict survival time for cancer patients. This involves using a topic modeling approach, which is a common technique in natural language processing and falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper involves some extensions to the standard LDA model, which could fall under the sub-category of databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of large datasets, which could also fall under the sub-category of computational epidemiology (cs.CE).
